        "title": "docs(himalaya): align v1.1 provider guidance",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- fix stale Himalaya skill examples that no longer match the v1.1 CLI\n- document provider-specific Gmail and iCloud guidance that matters for real mailbox access\n- keep the change docs-only; no OpenClaw runtime code changes\n\n## Why\n\nThe current Himalaya skill/reference docs still show commands like global `himalaya --account ...`, `flag add --flag ...`, and the old move/copy argument order. Those examples fail against installed `himalaya v1.1.0`.\n\nThey also underspecify provider behavior that matters in practice:\n- Gmail needs provider-specific folder aliases\n- iCloud needs different IMAP vs SMTP login shapes\n\n## Verification\n\nI validated the changed command shapes against a local `himalaya v1.1.0` install:\n\n- `himalaya account configure personal --help`\n- `himalaya envelope list -a work --help`\n- `himalaya message move Archive 42 --help`\n- `himalaya flag add 42 seen --help`\n- `himalaya template send --help`\n\nI also confirmed the stale forms fail today:\n\n- `himalaya --account work envelope list`\n- `himalaya account configure`\n- `himalaya flag add 42 --flag seen`\n- `himalaya message move 42 Archive`\n\n## Scope boundary\n\n- no runtime integration changes\n- no provider transport changes\n- docs/skill/reference updates only\n",
